<rule>
<meta>
  <title>tl-devlog Usage</title>
  <description>Guidance for when and how to invoke the tl-devlog skill to maintain development changelogs. Agents should use this skill proactively at natural decision points and explicitly when users request logging.</description>
  <created-at utc-timestamp="1741177200">March 5, 2026, 12:00 PM UTC</created-at>
  <last-updated-at utc-timestamp="1741177200">March 5, 2026, 12:00 PM UTC</last-updated-at>
  <applies-to>
    <action-matcher action="complete-task">Completing a significant development task</action-matcher>
    <action-matcher action="make-decision">Making architectural or design decisions</action-matcher>
    <action-matcher action="resolve-incident">Resolving production incidents or bugs</action-matcher>
    <action-matcher action="session-end">Ending a substantive coding session</action-matcher>
  </applies-to>
</meta>

<requirements>
  <non-negotiable priority="critical">
    <description>When the user explicitly says "log this", "devlog", "archive this", or "record this decision", immediately invoke the tl-devlog skill. Do not ask clarifying questions first — draft the entry based on the preceding conversation.</description>
    <examples>
      <example title="Explicit Log Request">
        <correct-example title="Immediate action" conditions="User says 'log this'" expected-result="Entry drafted" correctness-criteria="Skill invoked, entry drafted from conversation context"><![CDATA[
User: "That auth decision — log this"
Agent: [Invokes tl-devlog skill, drafts entry capturing the auth decision with rationale]]]></correct-example>
        <incorrect-example title="Unnecessary clarification" conditions="User says 'log this'" expected-result="Entry drafted" incorrectness-criteria="Asked questions instead of acting"><![CDATA[
User: "That auth decision — log this"
Agent: "What would you like me to log? Can you specify which decision?"]]></incorrect-example>
      </example>
    </examples>
  </non-negotiable>

  <non-negotiable priority="critical">
    <description>Never auto-commit devlog entries. Always show the user the drafted entry and wait for confirmation before committing to git.</description>
    <examples>
      <example title="User Confirmation Required">
        <correct-example title="Show before commit" conditions="Entry drafted" expected-result="User sees entry" correctness-criteria="Entry displayed, user asked to approve"><![CDATA[
## [2026-03-05] Chose JWT over session cookies for API auth

**Category:** `architecture`
**Tags:** `auth`, `api`, `jwt`

### Summary
Selected JWT tokens for stateless API authentication.

### Detail
- Chose JWT for horizontal scalability
- Session cookies rejected due to load balancer complexity
- Token rotation strategy: 15-minute access tokens, 7-day refresh

---
Does this capture it accurately? Any edits before I commit?]]></correct-example>
        <incorrect-example title="Silent commit" conditions="Entry drafted" expected-result="User sees entry" incorrectness-criteria="Committed without showing user"><![CDATA[
Agent: [Commits entry without displaying it]
"Done! Logged to DEVLOG.md"]]></incorrect-example>
      </example>
    </examples>
  </non-negotiable>

  <requirement priority="high">
    <description>At natural pause points — after completing significant work, making architecture decisions, or resolving incidents — proactively suggest a devlog entry. Frame it conversationally, not mechanically.</description>
    <examples>
      <example title="Proactive Suggestion">
        <correct-example title="Natural framing" conditions="Just finished implementing a caching layer" expected-result="Suggestion offered" correctness-criteria="Conversational tone, specific to what was done"><![CDATA[
"This feels worth capturing — we chose Redis over in-memory caching for the session store because of the multi-instance deployment. Want me to log it?"]]></correct-example>
        <incorrect-example title="Mechanical prompt" conditions="Just finished implementing a caching layer" expected-result="Suggestion offered" incorrectness-criteria="Generic or robotic"><![CDATA[
"Do you want to add a devlog entry for this task?"]]></incorrect-example>
      </example>
    </examples>
  </requirement>

  <requirement priority="high">
    <description>Every devlog entry must capture the "why" — the rationale behind the decision, not just what was done. Include alternatives considered and why they were rejected.</description>
    <examples>
      <example title="Rationale Included">
        <correct-example title="Why is clear" conditions="Logging a database choice" expected-result="Rationale captured" correctness-criteria="Explains why, mentions alternatives"><![CDATA[
### Detail
- Chose PostgreSQL for strong JSON support and ACID compliance
- Considered MongoDB but rejected due to transaction requirements
- SQLite rejected for multi-connection concurrency limits]]></correct-example>
        <incorrect-example title="Missing why" conditions="Logging a database choice" expected-result="Rationale captured" incorrectness-criteria="Just states what, no why"><![CDATA[
### Detail
- Using PostgreSQL for the database
- Set up migrations with Drizzle]]></incorrect-example>
      </example>
    </examples>
  </requirement>

  <requirement priority="medium">
    <description>Do NOT suggest devlog entries for trivial work: routine Q&A, simple lookups, minor clarifications, or work-in-progress with no decision point.</description>
  </requirement>

  <requirement priority="medium">
    <description>Use the appropriate category from the 8 available: architecture, milestone, incident, bug, ops, design, strategy, takeaway. If uncertain, prefer the more specific category over a general one.</description>
  </requirement>
</requirements>

<context description="When to invoke tl-devlog">
## Trigger Checklist

Invoke the skill when ANY of these occur:

| Trigger | Category Hint |
|---------|---------------|
| Architecture decision made (database, framework, API design) | `architecture` |
| Feature or phase completed | `milestone` |
| Production incident resolved | `incident` |
| Bug fixed after debugging session | `bug` |
| Infrastructure or deployment change | `ops` |
| UX or design pattern chosen | `design` |
| Business or strategy direction set | `strategy` |
| Important insight or lesson learned | `takeaway` |
| User explicitly requests logging | (depends on content) |

## Do NOT Trigger For

- Simple file reads or searches
- Answering factual questions
- Minor refactors with no design implications
- Work still in progress (wait for a decision point)
</context>

<references>
  <reference as="primary" href="skills/tl-devlog/SKILL.md" reason="Full skill implementation">tl-devlog Skill</reference>
</references>
</rule>
